---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import InteractiveChecker from "../components/InteractiveChecker.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Is This Website Legit? - Free Trust & Scam Scan - TrustChecker"
  description="Validate domain registration age, SSL trust indicators, active malware reports, and fake clone patterns before clicking links. Run a free trust check."
  activePath="/website-scam-checker"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-10">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="text-center flex flex-col items-center gap-4 select-none">
      <span class="caption-mono text-link font-semibold">LEGITIMACY AUDIT</span>
      <h1 class="display-lg text-ink font-semibold">
        AI Scam Detector & Website Legitimacy Checker
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-body max-w-lg">
        Stop phishing attacks before they start. Enter any web domain or URL to
        evaluate domain age, spoofing, and cybersecurity indicators in
        real-time.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Checker Dashboard -->
    <InteractiveChecker defaultTab="url" />

    <!-- Educational Content (Scam Guides) -->
    <section
      class="border-t border-hairline pt-10 select-none flex flex-col gap-6"
    >
      <h2 class="display-sm text-ink">How to verify website legitimacy.</h2>

      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-xs leading-relaxed text-body"
      >
        <div
          class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1"
        >
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
            >1. Check the Address Bar Spelling</span
          >
          <p>
            Scammers create lookalike URLs (called typo-squatting) to spoof
            popular brands. For example, `paypaI.com` (using a capital letter i
            instead of L) or `chase-security-update.com`. Always check the
            spelling letter-by-letter.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1"
        >
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
            >2. Look up the Domain Registration Date</span
          >
          <p>
            Scam websites are typically short-lived. A shopping or banking site
            registered only a few days or weeks ago is a major warning flag,
            regardless of how professional the page looks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1"
        >
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
            >3. Check SSL Encryption Presence</span
          >
          <p>
            Legitimate websites handling credentials use secure HTTPS
            connections (marked by a padlock icon). An insecure HTTP URL is a
            high-risk indicator for credentials theft.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1"
        >
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
            >4. Search for Contact/Company Details</span
          >
          <p>
            Fake sites often lack physical address records, standard customer
            service numbers, or transparent terms of service, hiding behind
            anonymous domain registrars.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
